### New Onboarding Page & Wizard

#### [NEW] `src/app/onboarding/page.tsx`
Full-page onboarding route. No sidebar, no header — clean branded canvas. Renders the `<OnboardingWizard />` component.

#### [NEW] `src/app/onboarding/layout.tsx`
Minimal layout for the `/onboarding` route — just a centered container with gradient background.

#### [NEW] `src/components/onboarding/onboarding-wizard.tsx`
The core 5-step wizard component. Each step is a separate sub-component rendered conditionally with animated transitions.

**Step 1 — "Who are you?"** (`StepPersona`)
- Role (dropdown: Founder, Marketer, Freelancer, Sales)
- Professional Bio (textarea — used by AI for voice)
- Why it matters callout: *"Your bio is your AI's voice. The better it knows you, the better it writes like you."*

**Step 2 — "What are your goals?"** (`StepGoals`)
- Clickable goal cards (Increase Brand Awareness, Generate Leads, Thought Leadership, Recruitment, Sales)
- Niche / Industry input (text)
- Keywords input (comma-separated tags)

**Step 3 — "Connect your AI brain"** (`StepApiKey`)
- Gemini API key input with masked display
- Link to: https://makersuite.google.com/app/apikey (opens in new tab)
- "Why do I need this?" expandable info panel
- Badge: ✅ Verified / ❌ Invalid (calls `/api/v1/keys/save` then validates)
- Skip option with warning: *"You can add it later in Settings. AI generation will be disabled until then."*

**Step 4 — "Connect a platform"** (`StepPlatform`)
- Platform cards: LinkedIn, Twitter, Instagram, Reddit
- Each card shows: icon, name, status badge (Connected / Not Connected)
- "Connect" button triggers same OAuth flow as integrations page
- Skip option: *"You can connect platforms any time in Settings → Integrations."*

**Step 5 — "You're ready!"** (`StepReady`)
- Animated checkmark + confetti burst (CSS only)
- Summary card: role, niche, goals count, API key status, platforms connected
- Single CTA: **"Launch my dashboard →"**
- On click: saves `onboarding_completed: true` to profile then redirects to `/dashboard`

